In this chapter on the File Manager, we delved into the pivotal role of this tool in locating game folders and essential data retrieval processes. The File Manager serves as a central hub for navigating specific directories, store managers, and the Windows registry to access critical game-related information. Through functions such as ApplicationByDirectory, ApplicationByStore, and ApplicationByRegistry, digital creators can efficiently locate and manage game assets across various platforms and environments. Additionally, the chapter discussed the importance of addressing subfolders within the root game folder, highlighting the ability to specify additional paths for enhanced organization and accessibility. Understanding the functionalities and capabilities of the File Manager is essential for digital creators to streamline asset management processes and optimize game development endeavors.